**Rival** | Unaligned Investigative | Limited Transformation

__Basics__
The Rival can only win when there are no other Rivals left in the game. 
Every night after Night 1, the Rival can investigate a player and will learn their role and if the investigation was affected by disguises.
__Details__
The Rival can only exist with another rival in the game. The Rival ascends when the other Rival in the game has died.
Every night after Night 1, the Rival can investigate a player and will learn their role.
The Rival is affected by weak disguises, obstructions and redirections. They are told specifically if the investigation was affected by a disguise, an obstruction, a redirection or none at all.
If the win condition of the Rival changes in any way, they do not require the other Rival to die. 
If the win condition of the other Rival changes in any way, the Rival still requires the other Rival to die. 

__Simplified__
Every night after Night 1, the Rival can investigate a player and will learn their role, the Rival can only win when there are no other Rivals left in the game. 
